1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 161, O.S.L.
2 2024 (25 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 90.29), is amended to read as
3 follows:
4 Section 90.29. A. If a federal law is passed that authorizes
5 states to observe daylight saving time year-round, Upon returning
6 to Standard Time on November 2, 2025, this state shall adopt
7 daylight saving standard time as the year-round standard of time for
8 the entire state and all its political subdivisions.
9 B. This section shall not be construed to affect the standard
10 time established by federal law governing the movement of common
11 carriers engaged in interstate commerce or the time for performance
12 of an act by an officer or department of the United States, as
13 established by a statute, lawful order, rule, or regulation of the
14 United States or an agency thereof.
15 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
